filter.help:
Here you can type filters with API like syntax. The filter accepts everything after the `where` keyword in a query.

E.g. to filter out tasks with a status `Approved` you can type: status.name is Approved. The field will validate the query and provide feedback if it cannot be parsed.

Please refer to the documentation about filtering to learn more about filter queries and how to use variables such as "{CURRENT_USER_ID}".

FROM context AS context_1 LEFT OUTER JOIN task AS task_1 ON task_1.taskid = context_1.id JOIN variable_register AS variable_register_1 ON (variable_register_1.topid IS NULL OR variable_register_1.topid = IF(context_1.context_type = :context_type_1, task_1.showid, context_1.id)) AND (variable_register_1.entity = :entity_1 OR (context_1.context_type = :context_type_2 OR variable_register_1.entity_key = task_1.object_typeid OR variable_register_1.ishierarchical = true) AND (variable_register_1.entity = context_1.context_type OR variable_register_1.ishierarchical = true)) JOIN custom_attribute_type AS custom_attribute_type_1 ON custom_attribute_type_1.typeid = variable_register_1.typeid LEFT OUTER JOIN variable_value AS variable_value_1 ON variable_value_1.entityid = context_1.id AND variable_value_1.registerid = variable_register_1.registerid 
WHERE custom_attribute_type_1.name != :name_1
